===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|þanc|lang=ang}},  from {{etyl|gem-pro}} {{recons|þankaz|lang=gem-pro}}. Compare Dutch {{term|dank|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Dank|lang=de}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{obsolete}} An expression of appreciation; a thought.

===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|þancian|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro}} {{recons|þankōnan|lang=gem-pro}}. Compare Dutch and German {{term|danken|lang=de}}.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# To [[express]] [[gratitude]] or [[appreciation]] to someone.
#: She '''thanked''' him for the lift
#* '''1900''', L. Frank Baum , ''The Wonderful Wizard of Oz'' Chapter 23
#*: The Scarecrow and the Tin Woodman and the Lion now '''thanked''' the Good Witch earnestly for her kindness; and Dorothy exclaimed:
# [[credit|Credit]] or [[hold]] something [[responsible]].
#: We can '''thank''' global warming for this weather
# To express [[frustration]] or [[annoyance]] with someone's words or actions.
#: I'll '''thank''' you not to lock me out of the house next time.

